</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Fine tune your Web searches
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   www.etour.com _ Do you need more than a search engine or a
newspaper's list of cool Web sites to make your Web browsing
experience more suited to your own needs. eTour, whose motto is
``Surf Without Searching,'' asks you to fill out a sizable
questionnaire and then offers sites hand-picked by scrappy human
editors to fit your preferences.
</P>
<P>
   www.send4fun.com _ Want to be the most hated person in your
office? Just use this site to mail overly cutesy, prefabricated and
ultimately useless mail in the vein of the famous ``Hamsterdance.''
There are special pages (''Thank You, Mother''), dance pages
(''Crocodile Rock'') and all-around fun pages (''Mission
Possible.'') We'd say more, if we could retrieve our bile and stop
gagging.
</P>
<P>
   www.dotcomfailures.com _ Hey dot-commers, don't get cocky. This
site is a reminder that for every eBay, there's dozens of companies
like Freewwweb.com waiting to fold. The site is a searchable
database of failing Internet company news, predictions and rumors.
</P>
<P>
   www.askOJ.com _ Oh dear. As if dot-com failures weren't
depressing enough, there is this juicy site, which promises live
chats with O.J. Simpson in which he answers questions directly from
readers. For a $7.95 fee, you can save yourself an advanced seat.
Let's hope it tanks, and soon.
</P>
<P>
   www.snapfish.com _ We've been promised a revolution in the way
we take photos for years, but maybe the revolution is in how
they're printed and viewed rather than the ``Say cheese!'' side.
Snapfish.com will send you a free mailer for your film, send you
free prints and then allow you to view the same photos online and
share them with friends. The quality leaves a little to be desired,
but the price is definitely right. (Reprints and doubles, however,
do cost extra.)
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
