   BATTLING-CANCER _ Eds.: Jim Morris is the outdoors reporter for
the Dayton Daily News. He spent the past three years battling
Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. In a two-part series, he recounts his
struggle and shares his insights about this fight for his life.
</P>
<P>
   I was scared to death. There really isn't any other way of
putting it. I could look back at the experience and say it was a
``piece of cake,'' now that it's several months in my rear view
mirror.
</P>
<P>
   But I won't. No cake here. If you want cake, go find Sarah Lee.
(Morris, Dayton Daily News) WITH PHOTOS
