<P>
   FARM-WOES (Clarksburg, Calif.) _ Gazing at acres of tomatoes
ready for harvest, farmer Jeffrey Merwin says he is living his
childhood dream of working the land. But his dream has turned into
a nightmare as he and scores of other farmers in Northern
California cope with the financial demise of their fruit and
vegetable-processing cooperative, the once profitable Tri Valley
Growers based in San Ramon. By MATTHEW YI.
</P>
<P>
   LORETTA-SANCHEZ-(Los Angeles) _ The Latino Committee 2000 brunch
this past weekend at Paramount Studios included almost every top
California Hispanic politician, but was notable for one no-show:
Rep. Loretta Sanchez. The second-term Orange County, Calif.,
congresswoman, blasted by the Democratic National Committee over
her plans for a fund-raiser at the Playboy Mansion, has kept a low
profile since the issue went public last week. By ZACHARY COILE.
</P>
