<P>
   _ with photo.
</P>
<P>
   NASALAB(Houston)_ The demand for astronaut training has
skyrocketed in recent years with the construction of the
international space station, but what most people don't realize is
that astronauts train for space walks by heading underwater. A
giant swimming pool that holds 6.2 million gallons of water is
where it all happens. By CLIFFORD PUGH. _ with photos.
</P>
