   TOFOG-REVIEW (AUSTIN, Texas) - Thirty Odd Foot of Grunts has no
hit singles, no major label record deal and sells its albums
primarily over the Internet. How can this indie country-rock band
draw 2,000 people, mostly women, to stand in line on a hot Texas
summer day for a concert at a barbecue joint? Could it be because
the lead singer is ``Gladiator'' star Russell Crowe? By MICHAEL D.
CLARK.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS-ARENA (San Francisco) _ San Francisco Mayor Willie Brown
has a grand plan for a sports arena on the waterfront but no anchor
team. Still, the mayor has invited a major Texas investment and
development group, Olympus Real Estate Corp. of Dallas, to San
Francisco later this month to lay out its vision for a 19,000-seat
arena south of the stadium where the Giants baseball team plays. By
ILENE LELCHUK and JENNY STRASBURG.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-49ERS-OWENS (Kansas City, Mo.) _ Terrell Owens, a five-year
receiver for the San Francisco 49ers, is exhausted. Not physically,
for his body is in the best of shape. Rather, Owens is dealing with
the emotional trauma of coping with the Alzheimer's disease that
has stricken a close and dear relative. By KEVIN LYNCH.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-JANIKOWSKI (Dallas) _ While Sebastian Janikowski, the
Raiders first-round pick, had his moments in Oakland's 21-20
exhibition victory over Dallas Sunday night, he also had some
others that made people wonder why the team felt compelled to draft
him so high and then give him $6.2 million, including a $2 million
signing bonus.
</P>
<P>
   OLY-SWIMMING (Indianapolis) _ The faster Dara Torres swims, the
hotter the suspicions become. Is Torres a phenomenon or a fraud?
Her sport has been polluted by performance-enhancing drugs, and now
every great swimmer sits under a cloud. ``Why do people have to
emphasize drugs because someone does something really fast?''
Torres said recently. Her coach, Richard Quick, has the answer:
``Unfortunately, that's where we are in sports today.'' By GWEN
KNAPP.
</P>
