kinder, gentler place. Indeed, things have changed so much for the
better in the Big Apple that I believe that the inhabitants of my
little West Coast paradise _ San Francisco _ could take some
lessons in civility from New Yorkers. By STEPHANIE SALTER.
</P>
<P>
   TOBACCO-HEALTH (San Francisco) _ In its continuing war against
Big Tobacco, the World Health Organization has just fired another
round. Although the war is far from over, the WHO's recent report
about how Big Tobacco has tried to subvert it will lower yet
further the tobacco industry in the eyes of the general public. By
ROBERT JAMES PARSON.
</P>
