   LANE-COLUMN-COX (Daytona Beach, Fla.) _ Everyone but the most
hardened partisans have decried the staged, smiley-faced
conventions of the major parties. Commentators have wished out loud
for the old days of platform fights, credential challenges,
delegate walkouts and red-meat oratory that lambastes the bad guys,
exalts the good and whips the faithful into spear-shaking battle
readiness. Well, be careful what you wish for. By Mark Lane.
