<HEADLINE>
BOOKS RECENTLY REVIEWED IN THE BOSTON GLOBE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``The Royal Family'' by William T. Vollmann (Viking, $40). A
sprawling novel set in San Francisco's wealthiest and sleaziest
demimondes, combining writerly dazzle with elemental humanity.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``The English'' by Jeremy Paxman (Overlook, $29.95). This
``portrait of a people'' is not a cozy bit of Anglophilia but a
bracing look at the English search for identity today.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Our Last Best Shot'' by Laura Sessions Stepp (Riverhead,
$25.95). Some advice, and a lot of understanding, about rearing
children in early adolescence.
</P>
</TEXT>
