 &UR; (Distributed by the New York Times Special Features) &LR;  &QC;
<P>
   &UR; THE REVIEWS ARE IN: &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   (1): ``We're not going to be like that `We Are The World'
convention in Philadelphia.'' (Pat Buchanan, Miami Herald, Aug. 8) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (2): ``You got Colin Powell making speeches, but you got Trent
Lott (i.e., a white Mississippian) making policy.'' (Jesse Jackson,
Newsweek, Aug. 14) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHY HE SHOULD BE PRESIDENT: &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   ``My great challenge was to convert Carl Sagan. I moved him from
atheist to agnostic. But I think he was just playing word games
with me.'' (Al Gore on his personal faith, New York Times, Aug. 6) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (TWO THUMBS WAY UP: &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   ``We've battled the image problem, and we're going to win the
election, because people realize what we're for, not what we're
against.'' (George W., Washington Post, Aug. 6) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; IMITATION IS...: &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   The White House claims nine parts of Bush's speech in
Philadelphia plagiarized Clinton speeches. Bush: ``Medicare does
more than meet the needs of the elderly; it reflects the values of
our society.'' Clinton (1997): ``Medicare is more than just a
program; it reflects our values.'' (New York Times, Aug. 6) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; A CONVENTION WORTH ATTENDING: &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   ``We were offering the Reform Party an energetic fighting
campaign, whereas the other side trying to block us at that
convention is simply mixing the Kool-Aid for the party. If I don't
get this nomination, it's pretty much the end of the Reform
Party.'' (Pat Buchanan on his primary ballot strife, ``Face the
Nation,'' CBS, Aug. 6) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ANIMAL-LOVER: &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   ``I think that's like saying that the veterinarian and the
taxidermist are in the same business because either way, you get
your dog back.'' (Joe Lieberman on why Bush's views are not similar
to his own, Aug. 8) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CUT THE BREAK-DANCERS: &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   One in two black voters claim the Republicans' allegedly
multicultural convention has left them with a less favorable
opinion of the GOP. Only one-fifth have a more favorable opinion.
Four in five think the Democrats represent blacks well. (USA Today
poll, Aug. 7) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PROTESTOR OF THE WEEK: &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   ``Congratulations! You just got on national TV.'' (Bush to a
woman who mooned his campaign train with ``Raise Minimum Wage,''
written on her buttocks, Washington Post, Aug. 7) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; IT WAS INEVITABLE...: &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   ``Mr. Lieberman would be the first Jewish person to serve
directly under a president since, well, since Monica.'' (David
Letterman, CBS, Aug. 7) &QL;
</P>
