<P>
   PRIVATE COUNSELING CAN HELP KIDS BOOST COLLEGE ENTRANCE SCORES
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGE-ENTRANCE-EXAMS-LIFEBEAT _ If there's one good thing
about the rising cost of college tuition, it's that it makes a
private college counselor or an SAT tutor seem cheap by comparison.
You've probably heard about these paid consultants who'll help your
child search for the right college and fill out the applications.
In 1998, the College Board published a study acknowledging that
coaching can improve scores on the SAT test _ which has a maximum
of 1600 points _ by about twenty-five points. By Ben Gose.
</P>
<P>
   THE PROBLEM WITH KIDS TODAY? TODAY'S PARENTS, SOME SAY
</P>
<P>
   KIDS-PARENTS-LIFEBEAT _ Dr. James Varga, a pediatrician, has
been in practice in Santa Monica, Calif., for 21 years, enough time
for a generation of well-educated, middle- and upper-middle-class
parents to have visited his examination room with their children.
His diagnosis of those parents: ``Absolutely too permissive.'' By
Karen Stabiner.
</P>
<P>
   VINTAGE ELECTRIC FANS ARE NOW HOT COLLECTIBLES
</P>
<P>
   FANS-ANTIQUES-LIFEBEAT _ Vintage electric fans have become
enormously popular with collectors in recent years. During the
early decades of the 20th century, electric fans were only used
either in commercial establishments or in well-to-do households. In
the 1920s, fans became more affordable and within a decade, they
had become decorative accessories for the home. By Jennifer
Riesmeyer Elvgren.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photos of vintage fans available in JPEG format by
calling William Gonzalez at 212-499-3355.) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   'THE WAR GENERATION' HAS SPECIAL PLACE IN HENRY FORD MUSEUM
</P>
<P>
   WAR-GENERATION-LIFEBEAT _ D-Day, Pearl Harbor, FDR, penicillin
and Orson Welles' ``War Of The Worlds'' radio broadcast. All of
these were part of growing up for the War generation. A new exhibit
at the Henry Ford Museum in Dearborn, Mich. called ``Your Place In
Time: 20th Century America'' covers people and events of the 20th
century. The second generation _ the War generation _ and its
accomplishments have received a lot of long overdue attention
recently. The exhibit brings that time in history to life with
photos, displays and interactive vignettes.By Mary Seelhorst.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photos of exhibits at the Henry Ford Museum in
Dearborn, Mich., are available on Newscom or by calling William
Gonzalez at 212-499-3355.)
