<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   DEMOCRATIC NATIONAL CONVENTION
</P>
<P>
   CVN-DEM-MAIN _ LOS ANGELES _ President Clinton and First Lady
Hillary Rodham Clinton are scheduled to address the convention.
(Shepard, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   CVN-DEM-HILLARY _ LOS ANGELES _ Hillary Clinton's speech to the
convention Monday night capped a hectic three days fundraising and
glad-handing, with a few surprises as well. (Vejnoska, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   CVN-DEM-BAXTER _ Is the bum's rush Bill Clinton is getting at
the convention a case of throwing out the baby with the bath water?
(Baxter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   CVN-DEM-GORE _ KANSAS CITY _ As Democrats begin their convention
in California, Al Gore is on the campaign trail in the nation's
heartland. The vice president will mark the 65th anniversary of
Social Security with a visit to the suburban Kansas City home of
former President Harry Truman. Later today, Gore will also join
running mate Joseph Lieberman for a rally in St. Louis _ the last
campaign appearance together for the two men until they meet up
again at the convention in Los Angeles. (Foskett, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   CVN-PROTESTS _ LOS ANGELES _ Security was heavy in the downtown
area Monday morning as police, remembering what happened on the
first day of the Republican convention in Philadelphia, brace for
protests. (Shepard and Vejnoska, Cox News Service). WITH PHOTOS.
WAN: Atlanta, National, Politics
</P>
<P>
   CVN-CERABINO _ LOS ANGELES _ Frank Cerabino's convention column.
(Cerabino, Palm Beach Post). WAN: Palm Beach, National, Politics
</P>
<P>
   CVN-MCNEELY _ LOS ANGELES _ Dave McNeely's convention column
(McNeely, Palm Beach Post). WAN: Austin, National, Politics
</P>
<P>
   CVN-TEXAS _ LOS ANGELES _ Texas Democrats go to work as the
Democratic
</P>
<P>
   National Convention begins, including 263 delegates who are for
Al Gore and five non-delegates here to back Gov. George W. Bush.
(Herman, Austin American-Statesman) WAN: Austin, National, Politics
</P>
<P>
   SUBMARINE-TOUR _The Navy celebrates 100th anniversary of
submarines andwe spend 3 days aboard a submarine. (Reid, Palm Beach
Post) WITH PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   TERESA-CHURCH _ ATLANTA _ A fight is brewing over the name of a
Nobel Peace Prize winner. A tiny independent Catholic church in
Woodstock has been calling itself the Mother Teresa Parish since
forming in March. That drew the ire of the Roman Catholic Church
and the Missionaries of Charity, the organization founded by Mother
Teresa. (Quinn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
