<P>
   STAR-DOC _ When Vladimir Chubinsky came to the U.S. in 1990, the
former Soviet wrestler turned physical therapist had no money,
spoke no English, and was supporting a wife and 4-month-old baby.
Now, he is a massage therapist to celebrities - including Jane
Fonda - and CEOs, and has developed a new fitness program called
``gravitational gymnastics'' that is part weightlifting, part
reflexology, and part energy healing. Chubinsky practices his
techniques with doctors, businesspeople, and celebrities in his
Sandy Springs Wellness Center. His clients claim amazing mental,
physical, and spiritual benefits, but scientists and conventional
physicians are skeptical. He is currently seeking a patent for the
system as well as validation from scientific researchers at GSU and
the Marcus Institute. Someday, Chubinsky hopes to bring his healing
methods to millions. (Kicklighter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
WITH PHOTOS
