<P>
   GLF-SERGIO _ Since finishing second at the PGA a year ago,
Spain's Sergio Garcia has struggled. He was supposed to be the new
challenger for Tiger Woods. But his golf game has gone south and
his attitude with it. While Woods has matured into a champion,
Garcia has acted like a spoiled brat. It has been one on-course
tantrum after another. He has a solid golf game but before it can
mature, he must mature. (Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   GLF-PGA-NBOOK _ Live notebook from PGA Championship at Valhalla,
in Louisville, Ky. (Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
