</P>
<P>
   FALL BOOKS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Summer 2000 may be remembered in the publishing
industry as the moment when longtime literary kingpins like Philip
Roth and John Updike saw their influence _ and selling power _
wane. So this fall and winter, the question arises: Who will
succeed these literary lions and become the next great American
writers? By JEFF GUINN. Story will move in ``e'' entertainment
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FLOCKHART-WOMEN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Calista Flockhart isn't near as flighty as the title
character she plays on ``Ally McBeal.'' She recently visited
Nairobi, Kenya, to do what she can to end violence against women
worldwide. By MIKI TURNER. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
