<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Tuesday, Aug. 15, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Gerry Hoppe at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   RECALL-TIRES (Los Angeles) _ Critics are wondering why nearly a
decade passed between the time problems with Firestone tires first
surfaced and this week's recall. It's not unusual. Nearly 1 in 10
Americans -- mostly children -- are injured by consumer products
each year. By Jesse Hiestand.
</P>
<P>
   FIGURES-STARWARS (Los Angeles) _ Even as a kid, Jason Labowitz
was very particular about how he played with his Star Wars action
figures: Half were drafted for battle; half stayed in the original
packaging. Now Labowitz and his brother cater to kindred spirits
out of a North Hollywood warehouse, as they cash in on the
evergreen market for Star Wars toys. By Robert Monroe.
</P>
<P>
   NESTLE-PDQUICK (Los Angeles) _ PDQuick, a leading direct-to-home
delivery e-tailer, today announced an agreement with Nestle for the
online ordering and express delivery of Nestle-brand products to
consumers at home or work. (Pam Park.)
</P>
