<HEADLINE>
SOUVENIRS, GET YER SOUVENIRS HERE
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 
 
By ELIZABETH SMILOR 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Words you don't want to hear upon your return home from the
Democratic National Convention here in L.A.: ``But, (insert title
here, i.e., Mom, Dad ...), you didn't bring anything back for me?
</P>
<P>
   ``Uh, well, you could have my `Gore for President' button,''
you'll say. ``NO!'' will be the definitive answer. While you might
understand the possible value someday of such a collectible, your
kids will just see it as an ugly symbol of how you forgot about
them on your really long journey.
</P>
<P>
   To help you avoid this scenario, we gathered some L.A. souvenirs
that are cheap ($20 or less), packable and fun. And here's how to
find these gifts:
</P>
<P>
   1. Hollywood glitz and glamour: Go to CityWalk at Universal
Studios Hollywood. Stroll into the Studio store, a host of other
stores or check vendors carts for everything Hollywood. Try All
Star Collections for sports memorabilia. (Note: If your kid's a
professional football fan, L.A.'s not your town.)
</P>
<P>
   2. Funky and Fun: Hop in your car and head to Venice Beach or
the Santa Monica Pier for really offbeat stuff. Tie-dyed L.A.
T-shirts, anyone?
</P>
<P>
   3. We Love L.A.: No time to spare? Never fear. Los Angeles
International Airport is jammed with souvenir shops. Crews of
California stores offer a big selection, and they're located in
several terminals.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
