<P>
   RUSSIA-TRAPPED-SAILORS (Moscow) _ More than 100 Russian sailors
were trapped at the bottom of the sea above the Arctic Circle with
little hope of rescue after their nuclear submarine was seriously
damaged in a collision, the commander of Russia's navy said. The
navy said it had begun a rescue effort in the Barents Sea on
Monday. In the early hours of Tuesday the navy was using small subs
to both inspect the damaged vessel and try to replenish the crew's
oxygen. Rescuers planned to attempt to evacuate the crew sometime
Tuesday, an effort that is expected to be complicated by the
extreme pressure that exists at the depth where the sub is lodged,
approximately 480 feet below the ocean surface. By Sabrina
Tavernise.
</P>
