crowd, reached the heights of achievement for its frat-boy readers
at a party it threw last week at the Farmer's Daughter Motel in Los
Angeles. Guests included such cultural icons as
 &UR; David Schwimmer &LR; , &UR; Kirsten Dunst &LR;  and  &UR; Carmen Electra &LR; ; the party
started at 8 p.m. By 10:15, cops in four helicopters were buzzing
overhead, followed by the arrival of police in riot gear and fire
marshals who shut the whole thing down.
</P>
<P>
   _ About 30 minutes before  &UR; Steven Spielberg &LR; ,  &UR; Kate Capshaw &LR;  and
their young'uns arrived at the beach in East Hampton last week,
reports Us Weekly, four men in chinos and white button-down shirts
arrived to lay the groundwork. They set out blankets, towels and
chaise longues, ``put up gigantic umbrellas and unpacked a feast
from overstuffed picnic baskets.''
</P>
<P>
   The Spielbergs arrived en famille, empty-handed, and spent two
hours there. After they left, the four men returned to pick up the
gear and cart it away.
</P>
