<HEADLINE>
BRADY TRAINED WITH TALENTED BUNCH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JILL PAINTER  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ Marcus Brady didn't have a typical offseason. The
Cal State Northridge quarterback lifted weights and participated in
drills with the likes of Cris Carter, Randy Moss and Dante
Culpepper.
</P>
<P>
   Brady participated in Carter's two-week program with some of
college and pro football's elite in Florida.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was fun,'' Brady said. ``It was the same thing. It was me
out there training and working hard to get better. I got to see the
level they're at and I feel I was right there with them at that
level. I've got a lot of confidence in myself.''
</P>
<P>
   On Monday, Brady was throwing passes to Drew Amerson, Gil
Rodriguez and a host of newcomers at the first practice for veteran
Matadors. Brady is expected to embrace the leadership role for
CSUN, which finished 6-5 last year.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's just fun to get back on the field,'' Brady said. ``In the
summer, when you first go it's exciting, but the summer is so long.
I was antsy to get back on the field.''
</P>
<P>
   Mitch Ryerson _ who's listed as the second-string quarterback _
won't be available for CSUN's season opener Sept. 2 at Air Force.
According to coach Jeff Kearin, Ryerson will serve a one-game
suspension for breaking a university policy.
</P>
<P>
   That means Jermaine Guinyard _ a freshman from San Diego Marion
Catholic High _ could be called upon, as well as walk-on Brandon
Martinovic. Kearin plans to redshirt Guinyard this season.
</P>
<P>
   ``(Guinyard) has a long way to go on the learning curve, but
athletic-wise he's up to the challenge,'' Kearin said. ``He's got a
lot to learn, but he's an intelligent player and an intelligent
student.''
</P>
<P>
   And Kearin has been impressed with Martinovic, a redshirt
freshman from El Cajon Christian.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm pleasantly surprised at the level he's playing at now,''
Kearin said. ``Mechanically, he's at a different level than where
he was in the spring. I'm excited and happy about that.''
</P>
<P>
   CSUN will practice in full pads starting Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   __ Minor injury: Defensive lineman Erik Gardner, one of three
returning defensive starters, has a minor hamstring injury, but it
didn't keep him from participating in two-a-days.
</P>
<P>
   __ Excused absence: Defensive tackle Johnny Acosta, a projected
starter, missed practice for personal reasons.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-14-00 2113EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
