<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, AUGUST 14 
</HEADLINE>
  (EDS: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.) 
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CANADA-DIAMONDS-NYT (Moved on Friday, August 11)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article that was sent on Friday,
August 11 about Canada's diamond industry misstated the title of
Stephen Kakfwi, the top official in the Northwest Territories,
where diamonds are mined. He is the territorial premier, not the
provincial premier; the region is not a province.
</P>
<P>
   BC-BELFAST-TOURISM-NYT (Moved on Friday, August 11)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article that was sent on Friday,
August 11 about murals in Northern Ireland that reflect the
conflict between Catholics and Protestants misidentified the
guerrilla group that killed Billy Wright, a Protestant commando who
is honored in one mural. It was the Irish National Liberation Army,
not the Irish Republican Army.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CHINA-POLICE-NYT (Moved on Sunday, August 13)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article that was sent on Sunday,
August 13 about a crackdown on political dissent in China misstated
the change in China's economic growth rate last year, when a slump
contributed to unrest in parts of the country. The rate of growth
dipped from about 8 percent to about 7 percent; it did not fall by
7 percent.
</P>
<P>
   BC-EUROPE-LAWYERS-NYT (Moved on Thursday, August 3)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article that was sent on Thursday,
August 13 about mergers among law firms in Europe and about the
success that American law firms have had in European mergers and
acquisitions misidentified a United States firm that did much of
the work on the merger between Daimler-Benz and Chrysler and on the
possible link between the Frankfurt and London stock exchanges. It
is Shearman &AMP; Sterling, not Sullivan &AMP; Cromwel.
</P>
<P>
   BC-STOSSEL-TVNEWS-MEDIA-NYT (Moved on Sunday, August 13)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article that was sent on Sunday,
August 13 about controversy over the reporting of ABC's consumer
and environmental correspondent, John Stossel, misspelled the
surname of a senior fellow at the Manhattan Institute who has
defended Mr. Stossel. The defender is Walter Olson, not Olsen.
</P>
</TEXT>
