Monday. Clinton is to address the Democratic National Convention
Monday night. (Monica Almeida/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT11) SANTA MONICA, Calif. -- Aug. 14, 2000 --
DEM-BLUEDOG-NYTR -- The conservative Blue Dogs are howling at this
convention, trying to position themselves for power should
Democrats gain the majority next year. Two Al Gore fans wave during
The Blue Dogs Democratic National Convention party at Pacific Park
at the Santa Monica Pier late Sunday. (Tony Ranze/The Lakeland
