   (NYT2) UNDATED -- Aug. 14, 2000 -- SCI-CITIES-WEATHER -- The
idea that cities generate their own heat and alter their own
climates as a result is not new. But now scientists scientists
using high-tech sensors have produced a more detailed picture of
just how human activities change the weather. A satellite
photograph, left, shows Salt Lake City and the foothills of the
Wasatch Mountains; an infrared image of the same area, right, shows
roads and buildings, in red and yellow. Blue and green correspond
to water and vegetation. (NASA/Marshall Space Flight Center/The New
