   (NYT1) ALLENTOWN, Pa. -- Aug. 14, 2000 -- SCI-AUTO-IMMUNE --
Autoimmune diseases, which are set off when an out-of-whack immune
system causes the body to attack its own tissues, strike at least
14 million Americans every year. Of those afflicted, the vast
majority are women. The causes of autoimmune disorders are unclear,
leaving patients like Dr. Catharine Shaner and her daughter, Laura,
puzzling over treatment. Patients need ``a real attempt to unearth
the underlying malfunction,'' Shaner says. (Salvatore C. DiMarco
Jr./The New York Times)
