<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GOOFY-ROBBERY-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK WOMAN AWAKENS TO GUN-POINT ROBBERY BY SUSPECT DRESSED AS
GOOFY 
</HEADLINE>
   By ELISSA GOOTMAN   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ In a sign that nothing in New York is free of
Disney's influence these days, a suspect dressed as Goofy is wanted
for a break-in robbery in the Bronx. And the bumbling, buck-toothed
character has an accomplice, disguised as either Elmo of Sesame
Street or Dr. Seuss' Grinch.
</P>
<P>
   But this is no Dr. Seuss story. The two suspects were reported
to be armed and considered dangerous.
</P>
<P>
   At 2:45 a.m. Monday, Theresa Dassa, 58, reported to police that
she awoke to find she had been joined in her second-floor bedroom
by someone in a full-body Goofy costume, and someone she reported
was dressed as Elmo, the squeaky-voiced Muppet. But she told the
police that costume was green, not red like Elmo, which led
detectives to suspect the Grinch.
</P>
<P>
   Dassa said she was not tickled to see them.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Dassa reported that the suspects pointed pistols at
her head and her ribs, and stole jewelry, a television and $600
from the kitchen. They also took her debit card, demanding the PIN
number. They then fled in her car, a 1996 dark blue Hyundai Sonata.
</P>
<P>
   ``When I opened my eyes, because I was fast asleep, I didn't
even know if I was dreaming or if this was really happening,'' a
shaken Dassa said later Monday. ``But when I saw the two gun
barrels pointed at me straight in the face, I knew it was real.''
</P>
<P>
   She insisted her identification of Elmo was accurate. Her
grandchildren are fans, she said.
</P>
<P>
   ``I could feel the furry costume against my skin,'' she said.
``They had the actual suits, like they wear in Disneyland,'' Dassa
said. ``I mean, this is why, for the moment, I thought I was
dreaming.''
</P>
<P>
   A neighbor, Virginia Farrell, said she rushed next door when she
heard the police arrive. ``A lot of people were saying, `Thank God
she wasn't hurt,' but she was,'' Farrell said. ``She was
hysterical.''
</P>
<P>
   Dassa's husband, Jack, died about two years ago. She lives in
the Country Club section of the northeast Bronx. There have been
several robberies in the neighborhood in recent months, said
Farrell.
</P>
<P>
   Last week, Dassa's other next-door neighbors awoke to find the
living room windows open and about $25,000 missing, the police
said.
</P>
<P>
   ``Between my house and her house, they hit Lotto,'' said
Jeannine Krzyck, 35.
</P>
<P>
   The police said it was not clear if the cases were linked.
</P>
<P>
   Goofy and his sidekick are still at large, and the disguises are
still a matter of mystery. However, Disney does make an adult-size
Goofy costume: it sells for $39.99 on the Disney store's Web site.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
